'''East African Examinations Council''' ('''EEAC''') was a secondary-level testing agency of the East African Common Services Organisation (current [[East African Community]]). The East African Examinations Council Act, 1967 established it.<ref>"[https://www.thecommonwealth-ilibrary.org/commonwealth/education/examinations-at-secondary-level/the-east-african-examinations-council_9781848591820-10-en  Examinations at Secondary Level The East African Examinations Council]." [[Commonwealth Library]]. Retrieved on October 12, 2018.</ref>

[[Zanzibar]] withdrew from the EAEC in 1970, and the [[Ministry of Education (Tanzania)|Tanzanian Ministry of Education]] Curriculum and Examinations Section briefly took over examination proctoring for Mainland Tanzania when it withdrew from the EAEC in 1971. [[National Examinations Council of Tanzania]] (NECTA) is now the testing agency of Tanzania.<ref>"[https://www.necta.go.tz/about About]." National Examinations Council of Tanzania. Retrieved on 11 November 2018.</ref>

