[[File:Élisabeth-Louise Vigée-Le Brun - Joseph Vernet (1778).jpg|thumbnail|Portrait of [[Joseph Vernet]] (1714–1789), French painter]] {{italic title}} '''''Four Times of the Day''''' is a series of four paintings depicting four times of the day: '''''Morning''''', '''''Midday''''', '''''Evening''''', and '''''Night''''' by the French [[landscape painter]] [[Claude Joseph Vernet]] (1714–1789).<ref name="AdelaideMorning">{{cite web|url=https://www.artgallery.sa.gov.au/agsa/home/Collection/detail.jsp?accNo=984P27%28I%29|title=Morning|publisher=www.artgallery.sa.gov.au|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref><ref name="AdelaideMidday">{{cite web|url=https://www.artgallery.sa.gov.au/agsa/home/Collection/detail.jsp?accNo=984P27%28II%29|title=Midday|publisher=www.artgallery.sa.gov.au|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref><ref name="AdelaideEvening">{{cite web|url=https://www.artgallery.sa.gov.au/agsa/home/Collection/detail.jsp?accNo=984P27%28III%29|title=Evening|publisher=www.artgallery.sa.gov.au|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref><ref name="AdelaideNight">{{cite web|url=https://www.artgallery.sa.gov.au/agsa/home/Collection/detail.jsp?accNo=984P27%28IV%29|title=Night|publisher=www.artgallery.sa.gov.au|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>
They were painted in 1757 in Paris, and are held by the [[Art Gallery of South Australia]], [[Adelaide]].<ref name="AdelaideMorning" /><ref name="AdelaideMidday" /><ref name="AdelaideEvening" /><ref name="AdelaideNight" /> The paintings consist of four separate scenes depicting morning, midday, evening and night,{{sfn|Lochhead|1982|pp=78–79}} a series created by several artists of the era including Vernet and [[Philip James de Loutherbourg]].{{sfn|Lochhead|1982|pp=78–79}}
== Artist == Claude Joseph Vernet was considered the leading French artist of his time in his genre, marine art and [[landscape painting]]. He came from a family of [[French painters]]: he was the son of a decorative painter, and his son Antoine-Charles-Horace Vernet, [[Carle Vernet]] (1758–1836), <!-- painted large battle pictures for Napoleon, notably the Battle of Marengo (1806, Versailles), and after the restoration of the monarchy he became official painter to Louis XVIII, for whom he did racing and hunting scenes. --> and his grandson [[Horace Vernet]] (1789–1863) were known as military painters. Vernet lived in Italy for 20 years, 1734 to 1753, where he had an atelier in [[Rome]]. His style was influenced by the Italian 17th-century painters [[Claude Lorrain]] and [[Salvator Rosa]]. His landscapes and especially seascapes were celebrated for their romantic qualities. Upon his return to France, a series of marine paintings were commissioned from him around 1753 by the French king [[Louis XV]]. This was to depict a series of [[seaport]]s, of which 15 paintings were executed. The project lasted for about 10 years, and until 1765 he traveled around France painting seascapes, eventually abandoning the project unfinished.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.museothyssen.org/en/thyssen/ficha_artista/588|title=Biography and Works, Joseph Vernet|publisher=www.museothyssen.org|accessdate=2015-01-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/encyclopaediabri27chisrich#page/1029/mode/1up|title=Encyclopædia Britannica, Joseph Vernet|publisher=www.archive.org|accessdate=2015-01-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://arthistory.about.com/od/from_exhibitions/ig/making_nature/moela_agsa_09_08.htm|title=making_nature|publisher=arthistory.about.com|accessdate=2015-01-01}}</ref>
== Paintings == In the series of four paintings, the first depiction is entitled ''Morning''. The painting shows a misty morning scene with [[fishermen]] with their boat. The second, entitled ''Midday'' depicts a sudden, unexpected [[storm]]. The painting ''Evening'' shows women bathing and washing their clothes. The final scene shows a rocky [[inlet]], with fishermen drying their nets while others are gathered round a fire. The scenes depicted in the paintings were Vernet's favourite scenes that he painted in different settings throughout his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/arts/yourpaintings/artists/claude-joseph-vernet|title=Claude Joseph Vernet|publisher=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=2015-01-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationaltrustcollections.org.uk/object/138286.1|title=National Trust Collections, Vernet|publisher=www.nationaltrustcollections.org.uk|accessdate=2015-01-01}}</ref> {{Clear}} <gallery mode=packed-hover heights=154px caption="''The Four Times of the Day''"> File:Claude-Joseph Vernet - The four times of day- Morning - Google Art Project.jpg|The four times of day: Morning File:Claude-Joseph Vernet - The four times of day- Midday - Google Art Project.jpg|The four times of day: Midday File:Claude-Joseph Vernet - The four times of day- Evening - Google Art Project.jpg|The four times of day: Evening File:Claude-Joseph Vernet - The four times of day- Night - Google Art Project.jpg|The four times of day: Night </gallery>
